  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>cucumber</strong> finely&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> to a sieve&nbsp;and sprinkle with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Give the <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>cucumber</strong> a good mix up and leave to drain over the sink for 10 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> sweet potatoes</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle with the<strong> nigella seeds</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place the tray in the oven for 25 min or until they're cooked through and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Combine 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong> in a bowl until dissolved&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once dissolved, add the <strong>apple cider vinegar </strong>&ndash;&nbsp;this is your<strong> pickling liquor&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> under <strong>cold water</strong>&nbsp;to remove any excess salt and give it a good squeeze&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> sliced cucumber</strong> and <strong>shallot</strong> to the <strong>pickling liquor</strong>&nbsp;and set aside until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>mint sauce</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl &ndash; this is your <strong>cheat's raita</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (or griddle if you have one) over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cut the<strong> brioche rolls</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> brioche</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and charred, then set them aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>butter</strong> has melted, add the<strong> curry powder</strong> and cook for 1 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pat the <strong>cod fillets</strong> dry and season with a little <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>cod</strong> and cook for 4 min in total, flipping halfway through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cod-sandwich-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, sandwich the<strong> cod</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>pickled&nbsp;cucumber</strong> and&nbsp;a dollop of<strong> cheat's raita</strong> in between&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>toasted brioche buns</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Skewer</strong>&nbsp;to hold everything together</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>roasted sweet potatoes&nbsp;</strong>with the<strong> remaining&nbsp;cheat's raita </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
